---
// Two places mobile data is protected by cryptography: at rest and in transit.
---
<figure class="figure">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 450 210" role="img" aria-label="Mobile cryptography protects data at rest on the device and in transit to the server">
    <!-- phone -->
    <rect x="55" y="55" width="70" height="115" rx="12" class="dgm-fill-surface dgm-stroke" stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
    <rect x="63" y="66" width="54" height="78" rx="4" class="dgm-fill-surface dgm-stroke" stroke-width="1"></rect>
    <text x="90" y="46" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-text" font-size="11.5" font-weight="650">Phone</text>
    <!-- lock at rest -->
    <g class="dgm-pop">
      <rect x="78" y="92" width="24" height="20" rx="3" class="dgm-fill-accent"></rect>
      <path d="M82 92 v-5 a8 8 0 0 1 16 0 v5" fill="none" class="dgm-stroke-accent" stroke-width="2.4"></path>
    </g>
    <text x="90" y="160" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="10">Data at rest</text>
    <text x="90" y="185" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="10" font-weight="650">FDE / FBE</text>
    <text x="90" y="198" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9.5">(disk encryption)</text>

    <!-- server -->
    <rect x="325" y="75" width="70" height="72" rx="8" class="dgm-fill-surface dgm-stroke" stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
    <text x="360" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="22">🖥</text>
    <text x="360" y="163" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-text" font-size="11.5" font-weight="650">Server</text>

    <!-- in transit -->
    <line x1="125" y1="112" x2="325" y2="112" class="dgm-stroke-accent dgm-flow" stroke-width="2.4"></line>
    <g class="dgm-pop">
      <rect x="213" y="92" width="24" height="20" rx="3" class="dgm-fill-accent"></rect>
      <path d="M217 92 v-5 a8 8 0 0 1 16 0 v5" fill="none" class="dgm-stroke-accent" stroke-width="2.4"></path>
    </g>
    <text x="225" y="135" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="10">Data in transit</text>
    <text x="225" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="10" font-weight="650">TLS / HTTPS · E2EE</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>Cryptography guards data in two places: <strong>at rest</strong> (full-disk encryption) and <strong>in transit</strong> (TLS/HTTPS, end-to-end encryption).</figcaption>
</figure>
